                                <date>1958</date>. С. <biblScope unit="page">??–??</biblScope>.</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><encodingDesc><tagsDecl>&amp;renditions;</tagsDecl></encodingDesc></teiHeader><text><body><entry xml:id="entry_kʼæʒ" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>kʼæʒ</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>kʼæʒæ</orth></form><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>кривой</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>crooked</q></tr></sense><re><re><form type="lemma"><orth>kʼæʒ kænyn</orth></form><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>сгибать</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>bend</q></tr></sense></re><re><form type="lemma"><orth>kʼæʒ-mæʒ</orth></form><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>криво и косо</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>crooked and askew</q></tr></sense></re></re><etym xml:lang="ru">Очевидна связь с <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/> <w>kāz, kaj</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xpr"><lang/> <w>kž-</w> <gloss><q>кривой</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><author>Henning</author><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_BSOS"/><biblScope>IX 84</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/> <w>kaj-maj</w></mentioned> = ос. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kʼæʒ-mæʒ"/>. Трудно сказать, имеем ли дело с исконным родством или заимствованием. Перебойным вариантом данного слова является <ref type="xr" target="#entry_xæʒ"/>. Может быть, сюда же <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kʼæʒīl"/> ‘хвост’.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Bailey._Asica"/><biblScope>30</biblScope></bibl>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">The connection with <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/> <w>kāz, kaj</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xpr"><lang/> <w>kž-</w> <gloss><q>crooked</q></gloss></mentioned> is evident (<bibl><author>Henning</author><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_BSOS"/><biblScope>IX 84</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/> <w>kaj-maj</w></mentioned> = Ossetic <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kʼæʒ-mæʒ"/>. It is difficult to say whether it is the congation or the borrowing. The irregularly corresponding variant of this word is <ref type="xr" target="#entry_xæʒ"/>. Maybe, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kʼæʒīl"/> ‘tail’ is related to it as well.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Bailey._Asica"/><biblScope>30</biblScope></bibl>.</etym><note type="internal">перебойный вариант??</note></entry></body></text></TEI>